Hi David,

Sure, confirming the staging is now updated. Let me know if this works for you?

Also 5pm sound good and accepted the invite.

Hi Joel,

Only one last change, is it possible to move up the results overlay so it is similar to the current implementation (as how it currently is in Staging makes the page longer than it needs to be).



This change shouldn't be a show-stopper to us pushing the page live tomorrow, although it would be great to rectify it before launch or a fast follow.

I know I mentioned 6pm for a coordinated launch on the 12th October, but are you ok if we bring that forward by an hour to 5pm 12th October?

I will send a calendar invite for us to jump on a call at that time so we can push all the relevant buttons together.

I will also be around later tonight if you need me to review the last change that was requested above.

Any q's please let me know.

Best regards,

David

Hi David,

We have now used the new values added to the API, thank you. We were calculating these dynamically based on the values that already existed.

Regarding the new Handover page, we have update our code, however, there appears to be a redirect in place which is forcing the current #before-we-continue-a-few-important-things.. page to load. If you do test submission you will see this in action.

Hi David,

Thanks Joel,

When I retested I could see it was resolved on the larger monthly number but not the first payment.



Furthermore, we have updated our endpoint documentation here to include the following

- Motor Quick Quote - This now references the additional values we return such as % saved, $ amount saved and first monthly amount. I can see that you have already picked that up, but just calling out for completeness
- Motor Quick quote Handover - This is a new page and includes the details of what you will need to update to bypass the duty of disclosure on our side. Please could you update this on your handover and let me know if you have any questions.

Best regards,

David
